[SN]TITLE[SN]
American boy meets life-saving bone marrow donor

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An eight-year-old American boy has flown half way round the world to say thank-you to an East Midlands teacher for a donation that saved his life.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
8 June 2015 Last updated at 21:52 BST
Leicestershire history teacher Jane Theobald donated bone marrow to Jake Larkin to help cure his blood disorder.
BBC's Rob Sissons reports.
